This event had a great impact on Colombia’s economy. The production of cocaine, gun smuggling, and the sackings of many towns’ businesses and homes had devastating consequences to the country’s businesses. Now, tourists can come and explore Colombia without fear, knowing it is a peaceful country and a paradise for paradise-seekers.

Thanks to this peace agreement, tourists can fly to Colombia duty-free, except for taking the international flight tax from Bogotá. But it wouldn’t be any problem for most tourists because they flew to Colombia because of its beauty and foreignness in terms of wildlife, ecotourism, and biodiversity.

Colombia is also famous for its storytellers called cuenta cuentos. That adventure and conservation stories with indigenous tribes help Colombia be proud of its past and present, all the efforts they made to free their land from violence and cruelty.

Why should you go to Colombia?

Colombia has many different travel destinations, many beautiful tourism spots and attractions, especially if you are into water activities, such as rafting, scuba diving, surfing, windsurfing, kayaking, and some other fun water activities that you probably didn’t even know existed before coming to Colombia. In this way, you have the chance to experience different aquatic adventures.
